COPY public.faqs (id, category_id, page, question, answer, order_index, is_active, created_at, updated_at) FROM stdin;
6	general	faq	Location	We are located in the mountains of Pérez Zeledón, about 4 hours from San José. From the city of San Isidro de El General, it is a 40-minute drive into the mountains on rural roads. After booking your stay, you will receive a detailed map and travel info.	1	t	2025-11-04 09:11:14.240178	2025-11-04 09:11:14.240178
7	general	faq	What is the weather like?	The climate at the ashram varies from cool and rainy to hot and humid. Mid-mornings are typically sunny and warm, with fog or rain often arriving around noon to mid-afternoon, followed by chilly nights and early mornings.\n\n Elevation: 1100 meters (approx.)\n\n Year-round (rainy & dry seasons):\n• Avg temp: 20°C (68°F)\n• Low temp: 16°C (61°F)\n• High temp: 29°C (85°F)	2	t	2025-11-04 09:11:14.240178	2025-11-04 09:11:14.240178
8	general	faq	What is your property like?	We are nestled in the mountains of southern Costa Rica. Our land includes tropical cloud forest, pastures, springs, rivers, organic gardens, and food forests. The terrain is hilly and can be muddy in the rainy season, but our roads, paths, and stairways are well maintained.	3	t	2025-11-04 09:11:14.240178	2025-11-04 09:11:14.240178
10	general	faq	What languages are spoken at Sat Yoga Ashram?	All of our classes are generally offered in English.	5	t	2025-11-04 09:11:14.240178	2025-11-04 09:11:14.240178
15	general	faq	How can I join the community?	Becoming a member of our community is a multistep process that can take several months or even years. Serious seekers drawn to the monastic life should first attend one of our onsite retreats. From there, we can discuss the process in person.	10	t	2025-11-04 09:11:14.240178	2025-11-04 09:11:14.240178
16	accommodations	faq	Is there Wi-Fi and cell phone service?	Yes, Wi-Fi is available in the main lodge and cabins. If you want cell service, ensure that your phone has international roaming, or purchase a Kölbi brand prepaid SIM card.	1	t	2025-11-04 09:11:14.240178	2025-11-04 09:11:14.240178
17	accommodations	faq	Can I bring my children?	No. Unfortunately, we do not have the facilities to accommodate children.	2	t	2025-11-04 09:11:14.240178	2025-11-04 09:11:14.240178
18	accommodations	faq	Can I bring or cook my own food?	We serve three vegetarian meals daily, and we offer a tea station and a small gift shop with snacks. Some visitor cabins may include a kitchenette or tea station. Please let us know if having a kitchenette is important to you and if you plan to bring food (vegetarian only).	3	t	2025-11-04 09:11:14.240178	2025-11-04 09:11:14.240178
20	accommodations	faq	Is the water safe to drink?	Yes. We offer potable spring water at our main building. Please bring a reusable water bottle for personal use. While showering and brushing your teeth with tap water is safe, we recommend not drinking directly from the taps.	5	t	2025-11-04 09:11:14.240178	2025-11-04 09:11:14.240178
22	accommodations	faq	Is there laundry service?	Yes. Laundry facilities and laundry service are both available for an additional fee.	7	t	2025-11-04 09:11:14.240178	2025-11-04 09:11:14.240178
23	accommodations	faq	Will I need extra cash?	Retreats are all-inclusive once you arrive. Most extra services (e.g., individual sessions and gift shop purchases) can be paid for by credit card or cash. External practitioners, such as massage therapists, may accept cash only. We recommend bringing $500–$1000 in cash, depending on your length of stay.\nPlease note: Costa Rican banks do not accept damaged U.S. currency (no tears, writing, or other marks), so we ask that you please bring acceptable bills.	8	t	2025-11-04 09:11:14.240178	2025-11-04 09:11:14.240178
24	travel	faq	How do I get to the Ashram?	We're located in the southern Pacific region of Costa Rica, in the canton of Pérez Zeledón.	1	t	2025-11-04 09:11:14.240178	2025-11-04 09:11:14.240178
25	travel	faq	What are check-in and check-out times?	Arrival and Check-In: Generally between 2:30 and 3:00 PM on the first day of the retreat\n\nDeparture and Check-Out: After breakfast on the final day of the retreat	2	t	2025-11-04 09:11:14.240178	2025-11-04 09:11:14.240178
26	travel	faq	What meals are included on arrival and departure days?	Arrival Day: Dinner\n\nDeparture Day: Breakfast	3	t	2025-11-04 09:11:14.240178	2025-11-04 09:11:14.240178
27	travel	faq	Do I need a visa?	Check with your local Costa Rican embassy or consulate for travel requirements.	4	t	2025-11-04 09:11:14.240178	2025-11-04 09:11:14.240178
9	general	faq	Whom do I contact for more information?	Please reach out to Amrita, our <a href="/contact" class="text-[#942017] hover:underline">Visit Coordinator</a>.	4	t	2025-11-04 09:11:14.240178	2025-11-04 09:11:14.240178
12	general	faq	Are scholarships available?	We have limited scholarships for on-site retreats. Partial work-trade opportunities may be available for extended stays beyond the duration of the retreat or for returning visitors, depending on financial need and availability.\n\nPlease reach out to Amrita, our <a href="/contact" class="text-[#942017] hover:underline">Visit Coordinator</a>, for more information.	7	t	2025-11-04 09:11:14.240178	2025-11-04 09:11:14.240178
13	general	faq	Can I come for a day trip?	No, we host visitors for a minimum one-week stay and only during one of our officially scheduled retreats. Please read more about our offerings at <a href="/retreats/ashram" class="text-[#942017] hover:underline">Staying At The Ashram</a>	8	t	2025-11-04 09:11:14.240178	2025-11-04 09:11:14.240178
14	general	faq	Can I extend my stay after the retreat?	You may apply to extend after the end of a retreat. If you're interested in extending your visit, speak with Amrita, our <a href="/contact" class="text-[#942017] hover:underline">Visit Coordinator</a>.	9	t	2025-11-04 09:11:14.240178	2025-11-04 09:11:14.240178
28	travel	faq	What is the closest international airport?	The nearest airport is Juan Santamaría International Airport (SJO) in Alajuela, near San José. It's about 140 km (87 miles) from Pérez Zeledón (3.5 to 4 hours by car or shuttle).	5	t	2025-11-04 09:11:14.240178	2025-11-04 09:11:14.240178
29	travel	faq	When should I arrive?	Arrive in San José at least one full day before the retreat begins to allow time for travel to the ashram.	6	t	2025-11-04 09:11:14.240178	2025-11-04 09:11:14.240178
30	travel	faq	Where should I stay in San José?	Some recommended options:\n• Tierra Magica (in Escazú, a suburb of San Jose that is close to the airport)\n• Airport Holiday Inn (airport hotel)\n• Airport Courtyard (airport hotel)\n• Fairfield by Marriott (airport hotel)\n• Honey Bee (close to the airport)\n• Casa Costa Rica Boutique B&B (close to the airport)	7	t	2025-11-04 09:11:14.240178	2025-11-04 09:11:14.240178
31	travel	faq	How do I get to my hotel from the airport?	Most hotels offer shuttle service. If not, use official airport taxis (safe and fixed rates).	8	t	2025-11-04 09:11:14.240178	2025-11-04 09:11:14.240178
32	travel	faq	How do I get to the Ashram from San Jose?	Option 1: Shared Private Taxi (from San José)\n• Pickup from your hotel, with a stop for lunch on the way.\n• Cost: $80–$100 per person (depends on group size and driver)\n\nOption 2: Private Taxi\n• Direct from San José to the Ashram (includes lunch stop).\n• Cost: $200–$225 per vehicle\n\nOption 3: Drive Yourself\n• If you're driving, be sure to have a 4×4 vehicle.	9	t	2025-11-04 09:11:14.240178	2025-11-04 09:11:14.240178
33	packing	faq	What to Bring	• Flashlight\n• Alarm clock\n• Reusable water bottle\n• Journal\n• Yoga mat\n• At least one white outfit for satsangs and special events\n• Outdoor clothes and shoes for permaculture\n• Bathing suit for possible river trips\n• Modest, comfortable clothing for classes, meditation, and karma yoga\n• Soft-soled shoes for wearing indoors; socks for meditation sittings and satsangs	1	t	2025-11-04 09:11:14.240178	2025-11-04 09:11:14.240178
34	packing	faq	What to Leave Behind	• Cigarettes, alcohol, and illegal substances\n• Hair dryers\n• Candles, incense, or anything with an open flame\n• Strong fragrances and scented products\n• Immodest or overly casual clothing (e.g., short shorts, thin-strap tanks, mini-skirts, etc.)	2	t	2025-11-04 09:11:14.240178	2025-11-04 09:11:14.240178
19	accommodations	faq	Can you accommodate special dietary needs?	We provide vegetarian meals, with non-dairy and gluten-free options available upon request. We strive to meet other dietary needs—especially medically necessary ones—whenever possible. Please coordinate this with our <a href="/contact" class="text-[#942017] hover:underline">Visit Coordinator</a>.	4	t	2025-11-04 09:11:14.240178	2025-11-04 09:11:14.240178
21	accommodations	faq	What are the housing options?	Guests stay in private rooms with either private or shared bathrooms in simple yet beautifully designed cabins. Each cabin holds up to three private sleeping spaces. Visit <a href="/retreats/ashram" class="text-[#942017] hover:underline">Staying At The Ashram</a> for more details.	6	t	2025-11-04 09:11:14.240178	2025-11-04 09:11:14.240178
35	atmanology	faq	What are individual Atmanology sessions?	These transformational sessions—offered by trained guides—are a cornerstone of the Ashram's therapeutic work. We strongly encourage all visitors who will be here for a week or more to participate in these sessions. Learn more about <a href="/about/satyoga#atmanology" class="text-[#942017] hover:underline">Atmanology Sessions here</a>.\n\nThe fees for these sessions are calculated separately from the retreat fee.	1	t	2025-11-04 09:11:14.240178	2025-11-04 09:11:14.240178
