1afdf3d8-0e38-4156-a975-bb12ec555071	the-unreality-of-the-world-a-fascinating-enigma	The Unreality of the World: A Fascinating Enigma!	It is now widely recognized in the fields of medicine and psychology that meditation is a powerful instrument for the management of stress, the strengthening of the immune system, and for the acceleration of healing processes in the body. Many clinical studies have validated the effectiveness of meditation not only for physical healing and the diminution of anxiety, but for the improvement of the quality of life. The sense of happiness and inner contentment has been correlated to the capacity to meditate and sustain states of serenity and stillness. But for the Sat Yogi, meditation implies a great deal more than that.	text	free	0	\N	\N	The Unreality of the World: A Fascinating Enigma!Transmitted through ShunyamurtiNow that a Nobel Prize in Physics has been given to researchers who concluded that the cosmos is not locally real, the question of what is reality has received an important new profile, a new relevance, given the very radical initial parameters of thought now available. Let us take a dive into the depths of the inconceivable Real. But be prepared: There is no return.What the physicists mean by declaring the universe is unreal is that when particles are not observed, they do not exist as such, but only as probability waves, or wave functions. This fact is then extrapolated to all particles that make up all material objects—and to reduce them to objects of consciousness.Consciousness, however, is not physical. It cannot become an object. It is only that which observes and reasons about what is observed. But since all scientific observations are motivated by a specific kind of curiosity and desire, it is important to add that all observations are likewise primarily the expressions of desire. Desire, in turn, projects the object that it seeks. So, the unreality of the world takes the status of a dream, or a field of dreams. Thus, the import of the Nobel Prize is the recognition that the field of physics itself has morphed into the study of the non-physical.But we are still in the shallows at this point. We must take several further steps down into the fathomless abyss, with no guarantee that we can stop our freefall anywhere.The next step is to recognize that physicists have also discovered that neither space nor time is fundamentally real. This further confirms the sense that the flux of appearances is a holographic illusion, a simulation, or a dream. But because it is all an appearance in consciousness, then the question becomes: Whose consciousness is dreaming us?In other words, the particle would not exist if the physicist were not there to want to observe it. But also, the physicist would not exist if he were not observed, since he is a material object in the simulation as well. Do we keep each other in existence by observing one another? The ego probably does believe that at a deep level, which is the reason for its underlying anxiety, and its need to be seen and desired.Since consciousness experiences not only a world of particles and electromagnetic waves, but an astonishing panorama of colors, forms, systems, events, textures, tastes, sounds, feelings, and an extraordinary palette of different possibilities, intensities, durations, and saturations, we must accept that the physicists are imperience-blind, in the sense that they can measure the phenomena of experience quantitatively, but they do not recognize that the subjective, qualitative dimension of their experience—or what yogis call imperience—is far more real than the mathematically-configured model of an external world that they assume that they inhabit. But the inhabitants of an unreal world cannot be considered to have any reality, can they? Therefore, they cannot be the true observers. Who, then, is the Dreamer of this mysterious dream world?Someone recently posed an objection to the conclusion of the physicists that the world is unreal, with the following example: If you are running outside on a dark night, you can easily stub your toe on a rock or a log that you did not observe. So, its appearance did not depend on a prior observation.True enough. I am not sure how the physicists would respond to that. But the Christian minister and philosopher George Berkeley’s reply was that God is the real observer. However, to avoid excess hypotheses, we can say simply that consciousness observes all, and in fact projects all, as an expression of its own freedom of creativity. No other god or power is required. Consciousness is all that can ever be known—and known only by itself, for itself, in itself, and as itself.Now we can drop into another level of the fractal, and recognize that the situation can be nuanced much further. Let us start by noticing how wondrous is the world, and thus that it is clear that consciousness contains infinite potentiality. But different persons have different levels and qualities of consciousness. There are sages, saints, geniuses, and heroes, and there are criminals and fools. Each being chooses the level of consciousness they want to reside in, choosing among so many different flavors, styles, and levels of potency, intelligence, creativity, joy, and purity of attitude—ranging from demonic to angelic and in resonance with the Supreme Self—which vibrate as different strata of consciousness.We also know from the findings of psychoanalysis—consisting of 125 years of research by multiple trained observers of the movements of consciousness—that what we could call ego-consciousness is just a tiny sliver of our total consciousness.The Freudians focused only on the repressed subconscious levels of the mind. They also had to theorize an agency of what we could call ultra-consciousness, that Freud at one point called the Censor. This internal intelligence agency decides what can be recognized and willed, and which ideas, drives, fantasies, and other mental phenomena have to remain repressed. It also determines what can be taken into consciousness and retained, and what must be forgotten, avoided, or misunderstood. It is necessary to add that many subconscious fantasies may harbor an urge to hurt oneself. That will somehow always get expressed. That is what Freud called the return of the repressed.So, it may be that the body in our counter-example was consciously focused on running, while the subconscious was projecting a rock that would cause pain—which gave enjoyment to a superego fragment abiding in the underworld.The Jungians parted company with the Freudians, because Jung activated his upper death drive and courageously looked both downward and upward, to envision the activity of a superconscious, archetypal level of mind, that is also intervening in actual events, causing synchronicities and other paranormal phenomena.And, of course, the ancient yogis, followed later by siddhas, avadhutas, prophets, divinized shamans, and great saints, ascended even further—in some cases to the highest vibrational frequencies encompassing total consciousness. Their findings have become inscribed in what are revered as sacred texts.There is no ego at that level, no language, no thought, no world. The Absolute Dreamer of this cosmic dream cannot even be imagined, except through mythopoetic discourse that is bound to be misunderstood and misconstrued, not only because of the ego’s lack of maturity, intelligence, and depth, but because of the ego’s appropriation of language to serve its will to power.Every level of consciousness will serve its own ultimate concern, and take that for its truth. But because the ego is a crazy quilt of fragments that vibrate in a wide spectrum of frequencies, there are always conflicting drives and thus, incoherence and self-sabotage. The Censor cannot hold the center. Sooner or later, the ego comes apart. In the same way, families come apart, societies and nations self-destruct, and now the entire world is terminating its fictional existence.But what is really happening—since our subject is reality—is the return of the repressed God-consciousness (or if you prefer, our Buddha Nature). It had to be repressed so that the ego could feel real for a little while, until its merit had become exhausted by the serial commission of bad karma. Having sold its ability to reason for a mess of jouissance, it is now in the clutches of the lower death drive, previously known as the devil. At the same time, the devil’s polar opposite, as well as its Dreamer, in fact, the devil is the Dreamer’s own Shadow, so now the Dreamer must return in the flesh as well—and is in fact returning to more and more individual shafts of luminous consciousness, who thus become liberated from the dream, awakened into joyous laughter and the empty fullness of perfect awe and wonder.That is the wedding of Truth and Beauty, otherwise known as Shiva and Shakti, and by many other sets of names. Yet the Real is Nameless. The Real is formless. The Real is timeless. And the Real is now redeeming all that is unreal, all the remnants of this sacred Creation, this masterpiece of drama, this divine romance, this impossible Mystery, this ultimate comedy of egos, and this spectacle of special effects—is now the play is about to climax, to consummate, to culminate, to self-annihilate, to explode in blissful light.The good news is: Nothing ever really happens, at all.Om Shanti\nTopics covered in this teaching:\nMeditation	https://www.members.satyoga.org/wp-content/uploads/sites/5/2025/07/The-Unreality-of-the-World.png	\N	2025-07-26 13:56:48	essay	\N	0	2025-10-28 15:31:24.317221	2025-10-28 15:31:24.317221	[]	[]	[]	\N	\N	\N	\N	\N	[]
a1ba3bac-643e-45bc-a45a-c77e26400d30	ecstasy-and-the-eschaton	Ecstasy and the Eschaton	It is now widely recognized in the fields of medicine and psychology that meditation is a powerful instrument for the management of stress, the strengthening of the immune system, and for the acceleration of healing processes in the body. Many clinical studies have validated the effectiveness of meditation not only for physical healing and the diminution of anxiety, but for the improvement of the quality of life. The sense of happiness and inner contentment has been correlated to the capacity to meditate and sustain states of serenity and stillness. But for the Sat Yogi, meditation implies a great deal more than that.	text	free	0	\N	\N	Ecstasy and The EschatonWritten in 2011.Language immanentizes the Eschaton. The hyperdimensionality of the Supreme Real is lost in the flattened intellectualized reflection that discourse forces upon our supramental intuition. To say that the Eschaton is upon us is to recognize that the Real Itself is morphing into the monstrous, invading our imaginaries, seizing up our symbolic defenses, and finally forcing us to face the beyond of language. We are entering that beyond, one way or another: through horror that is unspeakable, sadness that cannot control its tears, or infinite ecstasy that unfolds as the Eschaton embodied as the ultimate paradox that is the Self.Many people still want to waste time arguing—over how serious a crisis is this really; or whether any leader can be trusted to guide us through the transition; or whether the vaunted goal of transcendence of the ego is even more than a mirage; or if renunciation of egoic jouissance is useful, healthy, and a necessary part of a redemptive path; or whether grace will simply descend upon us all one day, no matter if we are meditating and fasting, or drinking beer and watching tv.Thankfully, there is no more time for such barren debates. Civilization is breaking apart; unpredictable catastrophes are occurring daily in every part of the world; the ecological die-off accelerates, murdering our oceans and our lands; the climate continues to morph our sacred planet savagely into a world that is uninhabitable, while armies and bands of guerrillas everywhere continue an irrelevant armed struggle, either to defend or to overthrow a system that is doomed no matter which side wins.There is no winning any more. There is no narrative that can grasp the enormity of this situation that is self-created as a karmic backlash to our existential malfeasance as a species. How can we explain the worthlessness of our lives to our children? How can we face them and admit that we do not leave them a future, that we have destroyed our home? There are no words deep enough to express the shameful feelings—were our hearts open enough even to have such feelings as we deserve to suffer.In a more creative time, operas would be performed about this Event. But there is no Wagner now to present this Egötterdämmerung of the Real, to compose a sonic tragedy about the decomposition of our world in the utter madness of petty bureaucratic sanity. New Guantanamos are being built to house the growing legions of our voiceless prophets of doom, while the media drone on about the drone wars, and drone-like we daily lose more of what is left of our souls. The Eschaton will not be televised, although we are already seeing reruns of its prequels.Yet the true Eschaton is not the mere end of a world, but the transcendence of the ultimate illusion, the Mahamaya. Apocalypse means uncovering, and what is being uncovered is the omnipotent Real that relativizes all our versions of reality, our phenomenal plane of petty concerns. It is a revelation that radically fuses life with death and time with eternity. The ego itself dissolves in the impotence of language to control or even grasp the meaning of this immeasurable Event.All our projects aimed at the approval of some Other are rendered laughable, even those intended for an extraterrestrial Other or a divine Other, let alone a human Other. The ego can do no one any favors, except by dying. There is no possible justification by works any more, except to provide a space in which egos can come to die in peace, to offer a requiem for souls in torment. All we are capable of understanding is that there is no way to understand all this, and the only payment acceptable is the renunciation of the ego. Silence is the final refuge.Acceptance can result—not of future death, of the ending of a world, but acceptance of the unbearable truth that nothing ever was: only a dream in the vast emptiness of cosmic mind.How many universes have there been before ours, utterly unremembered? How many planets have gone through a similar Eschaton as ours now faces? How many times has our own planet reached this point? How many lost civilizations still lie buried under layers of earth and fathoms of water? How much will we never know of this reality? Is not all history just a grand lie? Do we even know anything at all? Not even our own history as individuals is anything but a private myth. Yet all these narratives have somehow conspired at achieving the grandest climax of all, forcing the ultimate unmasking at this midnight of the world, the unmasking of the emptiness at the heart of all that is.Yet who is here behind all your own most tenderly cruel masks—what last edge of subjectivity is there to witness this final denouement? What holy or unholy ghost really runs the soft machine? Are you ready to discover That?Past all imaginings of light and love, past all mythologies of heaven and hell, past all dreams both collective and personal that we have futilely plastered over the black hole of the fast-approaching singularity, past all hope of some deus ex machina saving us from our fate, past even the peace of pain-free reflection on our destined demise, can we, at this last moment in which there is still margin of separation from the failed death of mere unconsciousness, resign our attention to the Absolute, and attain the Liberation that some unknowable nucleus that is beyond Being, yet within us, still pulses valiantly to realize?This supreme ecstasy that beats ever more intensely in the Heart, the ecstasy of freedom, freedom from knowing, from becoming, from yearning—this Ecstasy the ancient Shaivite sages called Anuttara, the total surrender to the ultimate and unsurpassable delight, the nameless, formless deliverance from even the cosmic mind, deliverance from the creation and from the nothingness before creation—this is the secret of the Eschaton.The true Ecstasy that no experience can reveal, that no entheogen can illumine, no eucharist can invoke, the Beyond that I forever am, is itself the Eschaton. Now Here This.\nTopics covered in this teaching:\nMeditation	https://www.members.satyoga.org/wp-content/uploads/sites/5/2024/11/Ecstasy-and-the-Eschaton.png	\N	2024-11-18 01:59:53	essay	\N	0	2025-10-28 15:31:24.320119	2025-10-28 15:31:24.320119	[]	[]	[]	\N	\N	\N	\N	\N	[]
39f695de-da7f-40cd-a299-17fb366a3538	deceptocene	Welcome to the Deceptocene!	It is now widely recognized in the fields of medicine and psychology that meditation is a powerful instrument for the management of stress, the strengthening of the immune system, and for the acceleration of healing processes in the body. Many clinical studies have validated the effectiveness of meditation not only for physical healing and the diminution of anxiety, but for the improvement of the quality of life. The sense of happiness and inner contentment has been correlated to the capacity to meditate and sustain states of serenity and stillness. But for the Sat Yogi, meditation implies a great deal more than that.	text	free	0	\N	\N	Welcome to the Deceptocene!For some time, critical theorists have declared that we have entered a new evolutionary period, that they refer to as the Anthropocene era, meaning that our biological fate is now dominated and determined by the human species, which has gained the capability not only to despoil our natural environment and bring about massive poisoning effects due to noxious geo-engineering, atmospheric pollution, genetic modification, and pharmaceutical genocide, but to cause the extinction of all life on our planet (assuming we are even on a planet).However, this theory is now passé, overtaken by newer technological developments that have been made public. The instrument that has brought us into this latest era of our seemingly aberrant historical journey is the invention of what is generally referred to as artificial intelligence (AI). The effects of this digital development began with robots and chatbots, not to mention sexbots, that can seem realistically human and actually deceive people as to their status. But now, the unfoldment has gone much further, with the advanced capacity for producing deep fake videos. Once upon a time, people believed that photos don’t lie. But now, photographs and videos can no longer be trusted to be authentic representations of real people. Not even AI can detect for certain whether a video is made by AI. Therefore, no apparent evidence of an event not personally witnessed can be trusted. We may be constantly deceived by deliberately manipulated delusions. Therefore, I am ‘christening’ our new era as the Deceptocene.This technological development has exponentially increased the ability of the agencies that control the mass media to censor alternative interpretations of reality and to produce convincing displays of seemingly conclusive and settled facts that in fact are false.Recent examples of such malicious tendencies that have been uncovered—or at least apparently so—range from the strange case of the disappeared princess Kate Middleton, around whom extreme conspiracy theories abound, due to the revelation of manipulated photographs, mislabeled photos and videos of bad look-alikes claimed to be of her but depicting another person, and the latest video of her sitting on a park bench that a number of credible experts in the field have declared to be a deep fake, with many aspects of the video that seem to prove that. Nonetheless, other seemingly objective analysts say they cannot be sure, but that they lean to thinking the video is authentic. Of course, the scandal that this has aroused has damaged the entire royal family, but Kate has not made any appearance in front of a sufficient number of living witnesses to put the embarrassment to rest.Even more recently, an apparently fake attack by Israel upon Iran has taken place. It seems that Israel had to save face after being hit by ballistic missiles from Iran, which was a retaliation for Israel’s bombing of the Iranian embassy in Syria. Since Israel did not want to suffer yet another, more destructive counter-attack by Iran, they chose to fly only a few harmless drones over Iranian territory, but then to use faked photographs of missile strikes, combined with news reports on all the mainstream US news channels announcing a massive strike on Iranian military and nuclear facilities. According to Iran, nothing like that happened, no damage occurred, no missiles were even launched toward them, and therefore, there was no reason to strike back.In such a case, it could be argued that the fake news prevented a catastrophe, and therefore was justified. But the effect on people’s trust in the news media was collateral damage that may be even more harmful—although, again, it could be asserted that it is long overdue that people stop trusting the news.So, the Deceptocene is in full flower. Once we add to the deep fake infamy a few other emergent theories, we can see that this goes much deeper than simply an artifact of AI. One example is the work of Mauro Biglino, a renowned translator of the Bible, who has demonstrated that all the translations of that text are faulty, and that the scroll is not about God at all, but is a description of an ancient alien invasion of Earth. That would be too mind-boggling to be believed, except for a plethora of other evidence both ancient and modern confirming the reality of extraterrestrial flying vehicles, crashes, interference with human military activity, abductions, animal mutilations, reverse engineering of super high-tech craft, materials, and equipment, and infiltration of governments.We could add to the list of anomalous phenomena the seeming glitches in the matrix that witnesses attest, the often persuasive evidence of the reality of the Mandela Effect, and the apparent revelation of the fraudulence of much of our accepted history, according to the highly sophisticated theory of Anatoly Fomenko, as well as other ‘phantom time’ theorists. To top it off, many leading physicists now accept that not only is matter an illusion produced by quantum wave functions that become collapsed, or frozen, by acts of consciousness, but that neither time nor space is fundamentally real. Some scientists go even further, declaring that the entire cosmos is a simulation.Of course, none of the above is certain. Probably an equal number of self-claimed authorities would debunk them all. Welcome to the Deceptocene! The Beatles long ago sang the anthem of the age: “Nothing is real! Strawberry fields forever!” But don’t eat the strawberries—they are covered with pesticides, if they are not entirely made of plastic.The question that arises in curious minds is: Why is all this happening now? What is the significance, if any? As might be expected, Sat Yogis have a simple answer. Let us begin with the understanding that the earliest ontological theory, which has been accepted in written texts from the beginning of recorded history (to use a now debunked concept) including the Vedas and carried forward in the Upanishads and is implied in the oldest agamas and yogic sutras: the theory that the world is nothing but Maya, meaning illusion. Indian philosophy, including the Buddhisms that spread throughout Asia, declare that the world lacks essential reality. It is, as the current crop of physicists now echo, only a simulation. Reality is empty of reality. Thus, we have come full circle. At the end of time, the concept that history began with is finally confirmed with overwhelming evidence that cannot be denied. Even if all the evidence is false, that too confirms the Maya theory. The very concept of evidence is evidently falsified. Once all of our beliefs unravel in this way, we start to lose trust in our capacity for reason itself. Even our logic has no foundation if this is a simulation, or a dream in some unknowable infinite Mind.But what if there is still one true element that cannot be denied? That is awareness itself. Even if our thinking is delusional, can pure awareness be doubted? Even to doubt it confirms it. Presence is ineffable, but is the very foundation of the capacity to doubt. We cannot know anything—except that presence, awareness, simple nonconceptual consciousness, somehow abides. According to the ancient yogic theory of Maya, nothing is real but quality-less absolute impersonal unmanifest presence, presence that can only be conceived as absence. At the end of time, we must return to the beginning, and to know that time never began at all—there is only timeless presence. But this presence has the creative intelligence to deceive itself into imagining itself as myriad forms of becoming in wild worlds of its own superconscious imagining, to get lost in amazing adventures in hells and heavens that no human novelist or dramatist could have conjured, even with the help of the highest doses of the most powerful psychedelic substances.But the yogis go even further: This Infinite Intelligence that is dreaming us all is not, in fact, unknowable. Simply by disengaging from the obscuring mental chatter of the character one is identified with, and coming back to silent presence, opens the portal to re-absorption in the Absolute Self. And this is the entire point of the whole creation—to awaken, to realize the eternal ultimate Self while still present in the dream field and able to act through one’s icon in the matrix. This alone has always been the goal of yoga. And the attainment of the goal brings an Aloneness that no ego still in ignorance of the Real can bear. The intensity of the Bliss of the God-Self is too much for anyone but God.And That is what You are.Namaste,Shunyamurti\nTopics covered in this teaching:\nMeditation	https://www.members.satyoga.org/wp-content/uploads/sites/5/2024/04/Essay-Deceptocene.jpg	\N	2024-04-19 05:04:34	essay	\N	0	2025-10-28 15:31:24.322101	2025-10-28 15:31:24.322101	[]	[]	[]	\N	\N	\N	\N	\N	[]
