706d2da6-b4c4-4b9c-b972-805d9e35cdf8	the-wholly-spectrum-of-seva	The Wholly Spectrum of Seva	Underneath the heading of Seva, many aspects of what service really is can be enumerated that we haven’t yet covered in this retreat. One is that service involves a life of simplicity. We serve through being simple, through living simply without unnecessary and ostentatious accumulations of things, we live with the accurate necessity that diminishes our footprint on this planet to the minimal so that all can survive in the best way possible. The more simply we can each live here at Arunachala, the more yogis can live here at Arunachala and be fed and housed etc. But simplicity has a purifying dimension to it, regardless to your way of life or where you live…	video	gyani	0	\N	\N	\N	https://www.members.satyoga.org/wp-content/uploads/sites/5/2020/05/3.jpg	\N	2019-06-30 22:38:40	video_teaching	\N	0	2025-10-28 15:31:23.841349	2025-10-28 15:31:23.841349	[]	[]	[]	\N	\N	\N	\N	\N	[]
3dc7ed59-a9cf-4197-a2d4-5ce977cb3028	through-thought	Through Thought	We come together but we come together to be alone, in the innermost core of our Being. In most other social organizations whether it’s society or subculture out there or most families, people are together in order to be enmeshed and to be full of noise and conflict and projection and alienation from the Self. Here we come together to return to the Self. To stop running, to stop blaming, to stop projecting, and to stop identifying with the people in our lives, because when we join an ashram we come to recognize that this world of bodies is the illusion…	video	gyani	0	\N	\N	\N	https://www.members.satyoga.org/wp-content/uploads/sites/5/2020/05/3.jpg	\N	2019-06-30 22:37:59	video_teaching	\N	0	2025-10-28 15:31:23.84276	2025-10-28 15:31:23.84276	[]	[]	[]	\N	\N	\N	\N	\N	[]
e4a7f84e-eb8e-4192-ba0b-c3de7f916abd	seva-saves	Seva Saves!	This retreat will be one in which we will be discussing a subject that goes to the heart of the yogic life, a life of Seva. It is a fact that Seva Saves, but we have to know what we mean by Seva and we have to know what we mean by being saved. Because Seva is not simply work, it’s not about being a workaholic, that is not service and in fact those who have workaholic tendencies, their service is to do nothing. There has to be a balance, because often if you are a workaholic means you are running away from yourself. Rather than serving God, you are running away from God… under the guise of serving God, and it’s important that we don’t do that. The action must be balanced with the meditation. (Event: Seva Saves! Retreat.	video	gyani	0	\N	\N	\N	https://www.members.satyoga.org/wp-content/uploads/sites/5/2020/05/3.jpg	\N	2019-06-30 22:36:55	video_teaching	\N	0	2025-10-28 15:31:23.84391	2025-10-28 15:31:23.84391	[]	[]	[]	\N	\N	\N	\N	\N	[]
f62d3d48-93b0-40d0-be7f-abbed048c740	no-other-community	No “Other” Community	Someone asked during the retreat about hypnosis. The ego is a state of hypnosis, a self-reinforcing hypnosis through the suggestions that the ego is constantly filling your mind with. That is why we say, at the end of every meditation, the words Aum, Shanti, Shanti, Shanti. The word Shanti means both peace and silence and it is said three times because the triple silence is necessary to shift the energy field. The triple silence… of outer silence, no intention of speaking to an other, the silence of the mind, in which there is no inner speaking between fragments of the ego or superego, and the Ultimate Supreme Silence of the Presence of the Supreme Self. It is when all those three levels are in alignment that the energy field shifts.	video	gyani	0	\N	\N	\N	https://www.members.satyoga.org/wp-content/uploads/sites/5/2020/05/3.jpg	\N	2019-06-30 22:35:52	video_teaching	\N	0	2025-10-28 15:31:23.845133	2025-10-28 15:31:23.845133	[]	[]	[]	\N	\N	\N	\N	\N	[]
