cd9cd8c9-6174-43c0-858d-915d5fed354e	the-yoga-of-love	The Yoga of Love	We teach how out of the original Sat Yoga emerged the seven principal yogas. But those yogas do not include bhakti yoga. But it must remain absent, because it is the secret yoga. It is the yoga of Love. And bhakti yoga must never become a separate yoga, because it is non-separation. As soon as it becomes some separate specialized form, it becomes reduced to rituals and ceremonies and mantras and chanting and holding hands and hugging and that sort of thing, and the real meaning of the yoga of Love is lost. The yoga of Love is the true esoteric yoga, the most esoteric of all. Without the yoga of Love, there is no raja yoga, it is an empty, futile, boring exercise in concentration, it is praja yoga, not raja yoga. Raja is the king, praja is the subject. We don’t want to do the yoga of subjects, begging for crumbs from the king. This is a kingdom of Love. (Event: Divine Love is Real Retreat)	video	gyani	0	\N	\N	\N	https://www.members.satyoga.org/wp-content/uploads/sites/5/2020/05/3.jpg	\N	2019-06-30 22:33:36	video_teaching	\N	0	2025-10-28 15:31:23.847216	2025-10-28 15:31:23.847216	[]	[]	[]	\N	\N	\N	\N	\N	[]
